Update March 24 - Climate normals

C. Susannah Tysor

24/3/2023

Flowering period predictions through 2100

As climate changes, flowering occurs earlier in the year.

I chose two Shared Socioeconomic Pathways - SSP 2: ~3\(^\{circ}\)C - intermediate emissions scenario - SSP 5: ~5\(^\{circ}\)C - very high emissions scenario

See “Warming by Scenario” figure on this website or figure SPM.1 in the latest IPCC report for more. I’m actually not sure if the SSPs in the new report match the ones in the old report

Under an intermediate emissions scenario, flowering occurs about 20 days earlier. Under a very high emissions scenario, flowering occurs about one month earlier.
